===Verb===
{{en-verb|worm|worms|wormed|worming}}

#{{intransitive}} To [[move]] with one's body [[drag]]ging the ground.
#:''We wormed our way through the underbrush.''
#{{intransitive}} {{figuratively}} To get (into) in a [[devious]] way.
#:''He wormed his way into the organization''
# {{nautical}} To fill in the [[contlines]] of a [[rope]] before [[parcell|parcelling]] and [[serve|serving]].
#: ''Worm and parcel with the [[lay]]; turn and serve the other way.''

